<MediaContainer offset="0" totalSize="5" identifier="tv.plex.provider.epg" size="5"><Video art="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/widescreen/3840x2160/around_the_acl_16by9.jpg" guid="plex://movie/69b20a3dc4e6176b32652803" key="/library/metadata/69b20a3dc4e6176b32652803" ratingKey="69b20a3dc4e6176b32652803" summary="ATA 208: Kansas City Bracket Breakdown, Officiating Insights, and Hot Takes Heating Up Signature #3 We’re headed to Kansas City, and this episode of Around the ACL is all about setting the stage for Signature #3. Meesh, Jake, and special guest Michael Gonzales kick things off with a deep dive into the ACL’s officiating program—what’s working, what’s evolving, and what players and fans should know moving forward. Then it’s time to break down the Kansas City Pro Singles and Doubles brackets. With stacked fields across all four brackets, we highlight key matchups, potential upset paths, and which players are in position to make a serious run. To close it out, the Hot Take Scale returns where the crew rates just how spicy these predictions really are. Will Chamberlain/Cano miss the Final Four? Is Matt Guy due for a deep run? Could a Top-10 player go two-and-out? And are Hodet/Landis about to take over the doubles scene? It’s all building toward one of the biggest events of the season—don’t miss this one." type="movie" contentRating="M/12" duration="3600000" originallyAvailableAt="2026-03-17T00:00:00Z" requiresConsent="1" skipParent="1" thumb="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/poster/2000x2858/around_the_acl_2by3.jpg" title="Around the ACL" userState="0" year="2026"><Image alt="Around the ACL" type="coverArt" url="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/widescreen/3840x2160/around_the_acl_16by9.jpg"/><Image alt="Around the ACL" type="coverPoster" url="https://img.static-ottera.com/prod/bbb/media_list/thumbnails/poster/2000x2858/around_the_acl_2by3.jpg"/><Genre filter="genre=620143f98578